<p>The actual data is appended with the above obtained remainder. So the data sent to the receiver is 100100<strong>001</strong>.
The received data is then divided by the generator polynomial at the receiving end and if the remainder is 0 there are no errors in data. As demonstrated above, the CRC algorithms requires <strong>XOR and shift operations</strong>. The proposed solution was to add a custom instruction to the existing MIPS ISA of the NiosII processor, for performing the modulo-2 division, to enhance operation of CRC (Cyclic Redundancy Check) algorithm. The proceding steps were:</p>

